algorithm with proÔ¨Åling data from actual Nek5000 runs on Mira.

4

Performance Analysis Based on Mira and Nek5000

In this section we carry out proÔ¨Åling experiments and analyze how our predicted performance
results, which use Assumptions A1‚ÄìA5, compared with actual performance as measured on
Nek5000 runs on the Mira supercomputer.
Nek5000 is a spectral-element thermo-hydraulics solver, here however we focus only on the
Ô¨Çow part given by the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations. Neglecting the force terms and
presuming the Ô¨Çow to be driven by initial/boundary conditions we have the following adjoint
Navier-Stokes equations:
